On Sun, 7 Jul 2002, Steve Blackham wrote:

> Need a little memory help here.  Checking the basic timing of this 2
> litre engine.  When we are at tdc (#1) which cylinder and valve do we
> check to see if this is the power or intake stroke?  (Which valve on
> which cylinder will have just closed? >or opened<)

If you're turning the engine clockwise, the intake of #1 will close 1/2
engine revolution before TDC on #1.  The exhaust valve will open 1/2
revolution after TDC.

George

